wikipedia_page.main: William Philip Honywood (15 April 1790 – 22 April 1831) was an English Whig politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1818 to 1830.

response: Honywood married Mary Brockman. Their son William Philip Honywood was also MP for Kent.

response: The son of the politician William Philip Honywood, he was born at Marks Hall in Essex in April 1825. He was educated at Eton College, before going up to Trinity College, Oxford. While studying at Oxford, he played first-class cricket for Oxford University from 1845–47, making seven appearances. He scored 88 runs in his seven appearances, at an average of 6.76 and a high score of 18. Honywood died at Westminster in December 1870.
